						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Rājarājadēva III: Year 6 = 1221-22 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is very much damaged. It appears to record a gift of land made by the king, to provide for all the services in the same temple and in the same place as occur in No. 307, etc., above. A number of signatories, including Aṉapāya Mūvēndavēḷāṉ, the <hi rend="italic">tirumandira-ōlai,</hi> are mentioned.</p>						

